A 38-year-old man, Dr. Ugochukwu Williams has declared his intention to run for presidency He boasted that over 100 million Nigerian youths would “kick out” the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in 2023 if he is given the opposition Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, ticket. The presidential aspirant said that over 100 million youths were ready and willing to join the bandwagon and ensure that the APC was voted out. Williams, who said he would introduce efficient technology-driven measures to tackle insecurity, made the declaration on Saturday while briefing journalists in Owerri, Imo State Capital. He opined that most presidential aspirants on the platform of the PDP, like Alhaji Atiku Abubakar and Gov. Nyesom Wike would support his aspiration as soon as the ticket is given to him. According to him, “The Rebuild Nigeria Project, with over 100 million innovative and creative Nigerian youths, will change the narrative. “We will unite the people. We will deepen the content of our democracy. We will rebuild our collapsed economy. We will make Nigerians the focus of development. “Our Government will expand our international vision. We will check the rampaging insecurity. We will restore Nigeria’s lost glory. And we will reclaim our dignity, destiny and pride as the giant of Africa.”